  "privacyIntro": "At {appName}, your Faragha is paramount. This Faragha Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect your personal and health-related data. By using our services, you agree to the practices described below.",
  "privacySectionDataCollection": "1. Ukusanyaji wa Data",
  "privacyDataCollectionBody": "We collect the following categories of data: • Personal Information: NJina Barua pepe address, Simu number, Tarehe of birth, and gender. • Afya Data: Blood type, aMzio chronic conditions, mDawa vital signs, symptom logs, and Triage results. • Dharura Contacts: Names, Simu numbers, and relationships of your designated contacts. • Device Data: Device type, operating system, and app version for compatibility and sMsaada • Usage Data: Feature interactions and anonymized analytics to improve our services. We only collect data that is necessary for providing our Afya companion services. You have full control over what information you provide.",
  "privacySectionDataStorage": "2. Hifadhi ya Data & Usimbaji fiche",
  "privacyDataStorageBody": "Your data is stored using industry-leading security measures:\n\n• Encryption at Rest: All data stored in our databases is encrypted using AES-256 encryption.\n• Encryption in Transit: All data transmitted between your device and our servers uses TLS 1.3 encryption.\n• Health Passport: Your health passport data is encrypted with a unique key derived from your credentials.\n• Msimbo wa QR Sharing: Shared health data via QR codes is encrypted and time-limited.\n• Infrastructure: Our servers are hosted in SOC 2 Type II certified data centers with 24/7 monitoring.\n\nWe do not store payment card information. All payment processing is handled by certified third-party providers.",
  "privacySectionGdpr": "3. Kuzingatia GDPR",
  "privacyGdprBody": "{appName} is fully compliant with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR): • Lawful Basis: We process your data based on your explicit consent and contractual necessity. • Data Minimization: We only collect and process data that is strictly necessary. • Purpose Limitation: Your data is used only for the purposes for which it was collected. • Right to Access: You can request a complete copy of your personal data at any tWakati • Right to Rectification: You can update or correct your data through the app sMipangilio • Right to Erasure: You can request complete deletion of your account and data. • Right to Portability: You can Hamisha your data in a machine-readable format. • Data Processing Agreements: Wote third-party processors have signed DPAs. • Cross-Border Transfers: Data is processed within the EU/EEA unless explicit consent is given otherwise.",
  "privacySectionYourRights": "4. Haki zako",
  "privacyRightsBody": "You have the following rights regarding your data: • Access: View Wote your personal and Afya data within the app or request a data eHamisha • Correction: Hariri your Wasifu information at any Wakati through Hariri PWasifu • Deletion: Request account deletion through Mipangilio > Data & Faragha > Futa Account. • Restriction: Limit how certain data is processed by adjusting your notification and sharing preferences. • Objection: Object to specific data processing activities by contacting our Data Protection Officer. • Withdrawal of Consent: You may withdraw consent at any Wakati without affecting the lawfulness of prior processing. To exercise any of these rights, contact us at privacy@vitalseker.com or through the in-app Msaada feature.",
  "privacySectionContactUs": "5. Wasiliana Us",
  "privacyContactBody": "If you have any questions or concerns Kuhusu this Faragha Policy or our data practices, please contact us: • EBarua pepe privacy@vitalseker.com • SMsaada support@vitalseker.com • Data Protection Officer: dpo@vitalseker.com • Address: {producer}, Data Protection Office We aim to respond to Wote privacy-related inquiries within 30 days.",
